### getAddressSpace() {#a635c01c48533d477ae9b693022687f14}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>uint32&#95;t anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;AttributorAttributes.cpp&#125;::AAAddressSpaceImpl::getAddressSpace () const</>}
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
Return the address space of the associated value.

<code>NoAddressSpace</code> is returned if the associated value is dead. This functions is not supposed to be called if the AA is invalid.

### updateImpl() {#a7cbda5cf91752204a847e5af0ba2ae48}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>ChangeStatus anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;AttributorAttributes.cpp&#125;::AAAddressSpaceImpl::updateImpl (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/attributor">Attributor</a> &amp; A)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
The actual update/transfer function which has to be implemented by the derived classes.

If it is called, the environment has changed and we have to determine if the current information is still valid or adjust it otherwise.

\\Return CHANGED if the internal state changed, otherwise UNCHANGED.
